oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Chattanooga during Civil War
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Print of a view of Chattanooga during the Civil War that shows military encampments and tents. It is from an original photograph from the Office of the Chief Engineers of the U.S. Army.
Chattanooga experienced several battles in November of 1863 before federal forces won in late November.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: United States. Army. Corps of Engineers
